    "summary": "Would you like CLIL to be implemented (even better) in your lessons or your organisation? I help CLIL teachers and schools to not only think about what CLIL activities can be done in the lessons but also do this on a consistent basis instead of being a 'one trick pony'.\n\nWHY I DO WHAT I DO\n\nCLIL has been around for ages, but a lot of CLIL teachers are still reinventing the wheel worldwide. And that is a shame. My goal is to get CLIL teachers to get in touch with each other, to find inspiration and ideas and eventually become better teachers. Not because they need to, but because they see what works and can adapt it to their situation.\n\nWHAT I CAN DO TO HELP YOU\n\nWith 15 years of experience teaching CLIL mathematics in secondary education in The Netherlands and having trained hundreds of teachers, I hope to be able to serve you by sharing practical and relevant ideas related to CLIL.\n\nIn other words: I am not a researcher or a lecturer. I speak from practical experience, share what works in my classroom and always make sure my training sessions are very practical.\n\nI help CLIL teachers, both in The Netherlands and abroad, to implement CLIL through both offline training sessions and online coaching sessions, supported by online training modules.\n\nInterested in finding out more? \nHave a look at what I do at my website www.clilmedia.com or just send me a message :).",
